  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nMillions of Yelp reviews held category-level behavioral signal, but raw star ratings alone obscured how sentiment actually diverged across business sectors.\n\n## Workflow\n\nDistributed ingestion & transformation → sentiment scoring at scale → sector pattern detection → stakeholder-facing strategy report.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **ETL:** 5+ Databricks/Spark pipelines transforming 10M+ data points with SQL, cutting end-to-end processing ~15 hours versus the prior manual workflow.\n- **Sentiment:** AFINN lexicon applied to 7M+ reviews with Spark, exposing star-rating vs. sentiment bias by category.\n- **Insight:** 3 sector-specific behavior patterns (restaurants, salons, retail) grounded in review-sentiment evidence.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nBridged Databricks ETL output to business strategy, translating large-scale review data into 3 actionable, category-aligned strategy directions."
